{"title_page": "Sorry (White Lung album)", "text_new": "<!--PLEASE NOTE:  the references in this article are in a list format, which means the data for the refs is in the References section, not in the body of the article.  If you add a new ref, please follow this format.  If you delete some text that includes a ref, please preview the whole page and check that you haven't created a ref error in the References section.\n-->\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Sorry\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[White Lung]]\n| cover      = White Lung Sorry.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = May 29, 2012\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Punk rock]]\n| length     = 19:00\n| label      = [[Deranged Records|Deranged]]\n| producer   =\n| prev_title = [[It's the Evil]]\n| prev_year  = 2010\n| next_title = [[Deep Fantasy]]\n| next_year  = 2014\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        =\n | type        =\n | single1     = ''Bag''\n | single1date =\n | single2     = ''Take the Mirror''\n | single2date =\n | single3     = ''Glue''\n | single3date =\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Sorry''''' is the second studio [[album]] by Canadian punk rock band [[White Lung]], released in May 29, 2012, on [[Deranged Records]].<ref name=int/> New Jersey's ''[[The Aquarian Weekly|Aquarian Weekly]]'' reported that the album \"earned them a hearty critical reception at SXSW\".<ref name=aw/>\n\n==Reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| MC = 76/100<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/sorry/white-lung|title=Sorry \u2013 White Lung|publisher=[[Metacritic]]. [[CBS Interactive]]|accessdate=February 28, 2015}}</ref>\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web|last=Cherrie|first=Chrysta|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/sorry-mw0002385264|title=Sorry \u2013 White Lung|publisher=[[Allmusic]]. [[Rovi Corporation]]|accessdate=February 28, 2015}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[The Austin Chronicle]]''\n| rev2Score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web|last=Winkie|first=Luke|date=March 15, 2013|url=http://www.austinchronicle.com/music/2013-03-15/white-lung-sorry/|title=White Lung|work=[[The Austin Chronicle]]|accessdate=February 28, 2015}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[Beats per Minute (website)|Beats per Minute]]''\n| rev3Score = 83%<ref>{{cite web|last=Wolfson|first=David|date=November 15, 2012|url=http://beatsperminute.com/reviews/album-review-white-lung-sorry/|title=Album Review: White Lung \u2013 Sorry|publisher=[[Beats per Minute (website)|Beats per Minute]]|accessdate=February 28, 2015}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[Consequence of Sound]]''\n| rev4Score = C+<ref>{{cite web|last=Hadusek|first=Jon|date=August 7, 2012|url=http://consequenceofsound.net/2012/08/album-review-white-lung-sorry/|title=White Lung \u2013 Sorry|publisher=[[Consequence of Sound]]|accessdate=February 28, 2015}}</ref>\n| rev5 = ''[[Pitchfork Media]]''\n| rev5Score = 8/10<ref>{{cite web|last=Pelly|first=Jenn|date=July 30, 2012|url=http://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/16897-sorry/|title=White Lung: Sorry|publisher=[[Pitchfork Media]]|accessdate=February 28, 2015}}</ref>\n| rev6 = ''[[PopMatters]]''\n| rev6Score = {{rating|6|10|full=Disc Plain yellow dark.svg|half=AwesomeTemplate.svg|empty=Plain Disc 20% grey.svg|rating=disc}} (7/29/12)<ref>{{cite web|last=Grossman|first=David|date=July 29, 2012|url=http://www.popmatters.com/review/160987-white-lung-sorry/|title=White Lung: Sorry|publisher=[[Popmatters]]|accessdate=February 28, 2015}}</ref><br>{{rating|6|10|full=Disc Plain yellow dark.svg|half=AwesomeTemplate.svg|empty=Plain Disc 20% grey.svg|rating=disc}} (8/20/12)<ref>{{cite web|last=Grossman|first=David|date=August 20, 2012|url=http://www.popmatters.com/review/161977-white-lung-sorry/|title=White Lung: Sorry|publisher=[[Popmatters]]|accessdate=February 28, 2015}}</ref>\n| rev7 = Punknews.org\n| rev7Score = {{rating|4.5|5}}<ref>{{cite web|author=Rich27|date=August 31, 2012|url=http://www.punknews.org/review/11456/white-lung-sorry|title=White Lung \u2013 Sorry|publisher=Punknews.org|accessdate=February 28, 2015}}</ref>\n}}\n\n*''[[Rolling Stone]]'' named the album one of \"The 10 Best Albums of 2012\", saying: \"Vancouver kids bang through ten bursts of female punk fury in 19 minutes, with Mish Way's hungry yowl leading the charge. Nothing fancy here \u2013 you get thrashed, you get bashed, you notice strange bruises all over your shins, then as soon as it's over you press play again.\"<ref name=rs/>\n*''[[Now (newspaper)|NOW Magazine]]'' report that the album\u2019s \"ferocious mix of snarling hooks and hardcore urgency (together, the 10 songs clock in at under 20 minutes) found sympathetic ears at publications as big as ''Rolling Stone'', and suddenly White Lung started getting invites to festivals like [[NXNE]] and [[Pitchfork Music Festival|Pitchfork]].\"<ref name=now/>\n\n==Track listing==\nAll songs written and composed by White Lung\n#\"Take the Mirror\" - 1:22\n#\"St. Dad\" - 2:15\n#\"Thick Lip\" - 1:47\n#\"Bag\" - 1:49\n#\"Bunny\" - 2:01\n#\"I Rot\" - 2:14\n#\"Glue\" - 2:11\n#\"Those Girls\" - 2:04\n#\"The Bad Way\" - 2:00\n#\"Deadbeat\" - 0:57\n\n==Personnel==\n*[[Mish Way]] \u2013 [[vocals]]\n*Kenneth William \u2013 [[guitar]]\n*Grady Mackintosh \u2013 [[bass guitar]]\n*Anne-Marie Vassiliou \u2013 [[drums]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist | refs =\n<ref name=rs>{{Cite news\n | title      = The 10 Best Albums of 2012\n | newspaper  = [[Rolling Stone]]\n | date       = December 20, 2012\n | url        = https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/blogs/pop-life/the-10-best-albums-of-2012-20121220\n | accessdate = April 22, 2013}}</ref>\n<ref name=int>{{Cite news\n | last       = Daniels\n | first      = David jack\n | title      = White Lung's Apology Tour\n | newspaper  = [[Interview (magazine)|Interview]]\n | date       = April 19, 2013\n | url        = http://www.interviewmagazine.com/music/white-lung-sorry/\n | accessdate = April 22, 2013}}</ref>\n<ref name=now>{{Cite news\n | last       = Trapunski\n | first      = Richard\n | title      = BC ban